history.content: Hmm good question. Like you, we're still learning the new system. I would start by double checking the section on classes.berkeley.edu. As you may know, just because there's a green circle doesn't mean there is necessarily seats in the section.

children.subject: Yup, I tried out many different sections and I keep getting the same result (unless a section being "full" counts other factors I don't know about).
Is there some other way I would be able to switch sections? I am afraid that the waitlist for the other class will be processed and I won't be able to get in because of the time conflict.

history.content:
I am already enrolled in CS 189, but I would like to switch discussions due to a time conflict with a class I am waitlisted for. When I try to edit the class using "Options", I get this message:

"Error: Unable to swap to this class - class is closed. The class you are trying to swap to is currently closed and there is no wait list available. Select another section or a different class."

The discussion is open, and as I said before, I am already enrolled in this class. How can I change just my discussion section? Thank you.
history.subject: Switching Discussions CS 189
